nd to the given binding key.\n   */\n  def instanceOf[T](key: BindingKey[T]) = instanceOf(key.clazz)\n}\n\n/**\n * A simple map backed injector.\n *\n * This injector is intended for use by compile time injected applications in the transitional period between when Play\n * fully supports dependency injection across the whole code base, and when some parts of Play still access core\n * components through Play's global state. Since Play's global state requires that some components are still dynamically\n * looked up from an injector, when using a compile time DI approach, there is typically no way to dynamically look up\n * components, so this provides a simple implementation of the [[Injector]] trait to allow components\n * that Play requires to be dynamically looked up.\n *\n * It is intended to just hold built in Play components, but may be used to add additional components by end users when\n * required.\n *\n * The injector is an immutable structure, new components can be added using the `+` convenience method, which returns\n * a new injector with that component included.\n *\n * @param fallback The injector to fallback to if no component can be found.\n * @param components The components that this injector provides.\n */\nclass SimpleInjector(fallback: Injector, components: Map[Class[_], Any] = Map.empty) extends Injector {\n\n  /**\n   * Get an instance of the given class from the injector.\n   */\n  def instanceOf[T](implicit ct: ClassTag[T]) = instanceOf(ct.runtimeClass.asInstanceOf[Class[T]])\n\n  /**\n   * Get an instance of the given class from the injector.\n   */\n  def instanceOf[T](clazz: Class[T]) = components.getOrElse(clazz, fallback.instanceOf(clazz)).asInstanceOf[T]\n\n  /**\n   * Get an instance bound to the given binding key.\n   */\n  def instanceOf[T](key: BindingKey[T]) = instanceOf(key.clazz)\n\n  /**\n   * Add a component to the injector.\n   */\n  def +[T](component: T)(implicit ct: ClassTag[T]): SimpleInjector =\n    new SimpleInjector(fallback, components + (ct.runtimeClass -> component))\n\n  /**\n   * Add a component to the injector.\n   */\n  def add[T](clazz: Class[T], component: T): SimpleInjector =\n\n[21 more lines in file. Use offset=111 to continue.]"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778166652062}, {"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_iBjHKMlKnyFtshgoas9QeQ4Q|fc_0155ae1979f02a5d0169fcab7bbef081909a22210e2e69f686", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/src/com.typesafe.play/play_3/2.9.7/src/test/java/com_typesafe_play/play_3/MethodUtilsJavaFixtures.java\ntests/src/com.typesafe.play/play_3/2.9.7/src/test/resources/logger-configurator.properties\ntests/src/com.typesafe.play/play_3/2.9.7/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_play/play_3/LoggerConfiguratorTest.scala\ntests/src/com.typesafe.play/play_3/2.9.7/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_play/play_3/MethodUtilsTest.scala\ntests/src/com.typesafe.play/play_3/2.9.7/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_play/play_3/ModulesTest.scala\ntests/src/com.typesafe.play/play_3/2.9.7/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_play/play_3/PathBindableAnonymous12Test.scala\ntests/src/com.typesafe.play/play_3/2.9.7/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_play/play_3/Play_3Test.scala\ntests/src/com.typesafe.play/play_3/2.9.7/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_play/play_3/QueryStringBindableAnonymous11Test.scala\ntests/src/com.typesafe.play/play_3/2.9.7/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_play/play_3/ReflectTest.scala\ntests/src/com.typesafe.play/play_3/2.9.7/src/test/scala/controllers/ApplicationLoaderTest.scala\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778166652066}, {"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_SQ20OX3MNuQ8sPqZvofk2IwH|fc_0155ae1979f02a5d0169fcab7bbef881909447edcc2ce9b11c", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage com_typesafe_play.play_3\n\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\nimport play.utils.Reflect\n\nclass ReflectTest {\n  @Test\n  def createsInstanceFromClassNameWithRequestedClassLoader(): Unit = {\n    val classLoader: ClassLoader = getClass.getClassLoader\n    val className: String = classOf[ReflectTargetImplementation].getName\n\n    val instance: ReflectTarget = Reflect.createInstance[ReflectTarget](className, classLoader)\n\n    assertThat(instance.message).isEqualTo(\"created through Reflect\")\n  }\n}\n\ntrait ReflectTarget {\n  def message: String\n}\n\nfinal class ReflectTargetImplementation extends ReflectTarget {\n  override val message: String = \"created through Reflect\"\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778166652066}, {"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_4NP3MdfA75rRszHxfyuDgBcs|fc_0155ae1979f02a5d0169fcab7bbf008190a76a8503220fbd52", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage com_typesafe_play.play_3\n\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.catchThrowable\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\nimport play.api.Configuration\nimport play.api.Environment\nimport play.api.PlayException\nimport play.api.inject.Modules\n\nclass ModulesTest {\n  @Test\n  def attemptsToLoadConfiguredModuleByClassName(): Unit = {\n    val moduleClassName: String = \"com_typesafe_play.play_3.LocatedUnsupportedConstructorModule\"\n    val reachableModule: LocatedUnsupportedConstructorModule = new LocatedUnsupportedConstructorModule(\"reachable\")\n    assertThat(reachableModule.marker).isEqualTo(\"reachable\")\n    assertThat(classOf[LocatedUnsupportedConstructorModule].getName).isEqualTo(moduleClassName)\n\n    val classLoader: ClassLoader = new LocatedModuleClassLoader(getClass.